Handling
1. Solvent based inks are combustible and highly flammable. Precautionary steps should be taken to prevent electrostatic charges from building up and subsequently discharge them.
2. All solvent-based inks are with few exceptions are hazardous and special safety measures should be taken. Normal Industrial Hygiene and safety precautions must be observed and any form of pollution avoided.
3. Shelf-life of inks in original sealed container is six months. Inks are recommended to store at room temperature and keep container tightly closed.
Please refer SDS for more details.
4. Only suitable for use on the non-food contact side of food packaging.
